review_text: Verdun is a town that does not lack public spaces, especially the long green stretches that run along the St-Lawrence. People who live in the town or don't have that long to drive use Turtle Wharf Park regularly, be it for walks along the river, bike rides along its very long and very spacious bicycle paths, as a picnic site with the family, for its petanque courts,  or simply as a place to relax and watch the world go by.

The playground is nice, safe to use for the young children and the sprinklers are very appreciated by the kids of every age.
